Content:
Richard P. Graves (October 1906  June 6, 1989) was a veteran director of the League of California Cities. He became executive director in 1933. In 1954, he ran for Governor of California against incumbent Goodwin J. Knight. His campaign director was Pierre Salinger, who later served as JFK's press secretary. He later moved to Philadelphia where he started the Philadelphia Industrial Development Corp. After this he got involved in real estate. He would later return to Los Angeles, to continue his career in real estate. He and his second wife, Helen McDermott Graves, rode on Air Force One with President John F. Kennedy in December 1961. Graves was also a graduate of the University of California, Berkeley in 1931. 
